- What subject is this?
- Physics.

84
00:05:54,380 --> 00:05:56,093
Chemistry.

85
00:05:56,093 --> 00:05:57,643
Biology.

86
00:05:58,540 --> 00:06:01,329
Biology? You better learn not to lose your life.

87
00:06:01,329 --> 00:06:03,564
You skipped school to audition again, didn't you?

88
00:06:03,564 --> 00:06:05,381
No, Mom.

89
00:06:17,830 --> 00:06:20,521
- Thank you.
- You did really great.

90
00:06:20,521 --> 00:06:23,162
I think you have a bright future ahead of you.

91
00:06:23,162 --> 00:06:26,946
Our team will get back to you.

92
00:06:26,946 --> 00:06:29,028
I didn't want to lie to you,

93
00:06:29,028 --> 00:06:32,712
but if I pass this audition,
I'll get to become an idol for sure.

94
00:06:32,712 --> 00:06:37,830
You're so afraid of failing the audition
that you're willing to fail the exam?

95
00:06:37,830 --> 00:06:39,513
How did you know that?

96
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:46,745
Let's talk about how you did your exam
because you're not interested in being smart.

97
00:06:46,745 --> 00:06:48,480
The teacher called me.

98
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:50,592
Prepare to retake the exam.

99
00:06:50,592 --> 00:06:54,135
If you don't pass this subject,
you won't graduate.

100
00:06:56,700 --> 00:07:00,432
Moo, if you keep ignoring your studies like this,

101
00:07:00,432 --> 00:07:02,997
you'll regret it one day.

102
00:07:04,180 --> 00:07:07,400
Studies can be your plan B.

103
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:11,937
But I don't want a plan B.
My only goal is to become an idol.

104
00:07:18,100 --> 00:07:21,440
It's my fault for being too easy on you
that you got used to it.

105
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:23,524
I let this go on for too long
that you became so stubborn.

106
00:07:23,524 --> 00:07:26,414
Your grades have been dropping
since you started grade 10.

107
00:07:26,414 --> 00:07:30,404
You're now in the first semester of grade 12
and they're not getting better.

108
00:07:30,404 --> 00:07:35,206
I guess I have to give you
a harsh punishment this time.

109
00:07:43,290 --> 00:07:46,440
Mom, are you really going to punish me this way?

110
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:48,970
Yes. You will move to a school out of town.

111
00:07:48,970 --> 00:07:52,218
You will live far away you can't skip school
and go dancing anywhere.

112
00:07:52,218 --> 00:07:54,140
Grab that.

113
00:07:55,050 --> 00:07:57,057
And this semester...

114
00:07:57,057 --> 00:07:58,321
Careful.

115
00:07:58,321 --> 00:08:03,000
And if you ignore your studies this semester
and fail to get into university,

116
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:06,080
you can forget about dancing.

117
00:08:10,250 --> 00:08:13,100
Mom, tell me honestly.

118
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:16,989
Why don't you want me to dance?

119
00:08:16,989 --> 00:08:19,237
Because I love you.

120
00:08:19,237 --> 00:08:20,632
I'm in the industry.

121
00:08:20,632 --> 00:08:25,278
Outsiders think it's beautiful,
but it's actually not pleasant to be in.

122
00:08:25,278 --> 00:08:28,667
You'd have to sacrifice a lot more than you think.

123
00:08:28,667 --> 00:08:30,000
Trust me.

124
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,078
You can't be an idol forever.

125
00:08:32,078 --> 00:08:37,103
When you turn 30, 40, and 50, your time is up.

126
00:08:37,103 --> 00:08:41,744
Mom, I don't know what I want to be at those ages,

127
00:08:41,744 --> 00:08:47,152
but I know what I want to be now.

128
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:50,495
No more talking.

129
00:08:50,495 --> 00:08:51,690
It's just one semester.

130
00:08:51,690 --> 00:08:55,075
Go and study there so there's no entertainment
to distract you.

131
00:08:55,075 --> 00:08:59,157
Just focus on doing well in school and
passing the university admission exam.

132
00:08:59,157 --> 00:09:02,472
That's enough. End of story.

133
00:09:02,472 --> 00:09:06,364
Mom, you won't change your mind
no matter what I say, right?

134
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:12,360
If your dream is really important to you,

135
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:14,900
