259
00:17:08,709 --> 00:17:10,571
Here.

260
00:17:10,571 --> 00:17:14,190
Can you put this in a drawer? I'll lie down a bit.

261
00:17:24,450 --> 00:17:26,056
Excuse me.

262
00:17:40,158 --> 00:17:41,558
Hmm?

263
00:17:41,558 --> 00:17:43,643
Do you have a toothbrush for sale?

264
00:17:48,858 --> 00:17:52,464
You want to buy a toothbrush
at a rice and curry restaurant?

265
00:17:55,916 --> 00:17:57,346
It's okay if you don't have it.

266
00:17:57,346 --> 00:17:58,488
I have it.

267
00:17:59,513 --> 00:18:00,749
Just a moment.

268
00:18:02,784 --> 00:18:04,548
It's surprisingly available.

269
00:18:19,210 --> 00:18:20,288
Here.

270
00:18:22,069 --> 00:18:23,301
Thank you.

271
00:18:24,368 --> 00:18:26,216
- How much is this?
- 2 million.

272
00:18:26,216 --> 00:18:28,303
Huh? 2 million?

273
00:18:28,303 --> 00:18:30,665
If you don't have that much money,
you don't have to pay.

274
00:18:32,113 --> 00:18:34,775
A toothbrush shouldn't cost as much as 2 million.

275
00:18:34,775 --> 00:18:37,069
Stop. Don't move.

276
00:19:06,609 --> 00:19:07,843
It's just a mosquito.

277
00:19:09,970 --> 00:19:11,574
You startled me.

278
00:19:11,574 --> 00:19:14,140
You could've told me there was a mosquito.
I would've slapped it.

279
00:19:14,140 --> 00:19:17,170
Why would you slap it? You can just shoo it away.

280
00:19:18,676 --> 00:19:21,499
Can I help you with anything else?

281
00:19:23,619 --> 00:19:25,727
Is there a bicycle shop around here?

282
00:19:27,904 --> 00:19:30,404
What? He looks like he doesn't want to tell me.

283
00:19:32,422 --> 00:19:34,784
Damn! This is so far.

284
00:19:34,784 --> 00:19:36,744
I thought he said it was around here.

285
00:19:42,260 --> 00:19:43,898
What's wrong with my internet?

286
00:19:51,185 --> 00:19:52,824
Which way do I go next?

287
00:19:56,517 --> 00:19:57,878
I don't know.

288
00:19:59,639 --> 00:20:00,733
It's hot.

289
00:20:02,584 --> 00:20:03,765
Oh, hey.

290
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,957
I thought you said it was around here.
I can't find it.

291
00:20:07,957 --> 00:20:10,632
I knew you would get lost. Get on.

292
00:20:10,632 --> 00:20:13,267
- Are you giving me a ride?
- I guess I rode here to say hi.

293
00:20:13,267 --> 00:20:14,793
Hurry up. It's hot.

294
00:20:14,793 --> 00:20:15,932
Thank you.

295
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:24,984
Oh, this really is a bicycle shop.

296
00:20:24,984 --> 00:20:26,893
I told you it was nearby.

297
00:20:33,721 --> 00:20:36,961
Thank you. You're so kind.

298
00:20:36,961 --> 00:20:39,080
No. This will be 2 million.

299
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:40,659
Plus another 2 million
for the toothbrush from earlier.

300
00:20:40,659 --> 00:20:41,969
You're kidding, right?

301
00:20:49,085 --> 00:20:50,784
I didn't expect you to believe it.

302
00:20:50,784 --> 00:20:54,610
You should smile a lot.
You look so cute when you smile.

303
00:20:55,981 --> 00:20:57,928
Why is my face your problem?

304
00:20:57,928 --> 00:21:01,241
Just go in. I'll wait outside.

305
00:21:01,241 --> 00:21:02,346
Okay.

306
00:21:10,701 --> 00:21:12,878
I look kinda cute when I smile.

307
00:21:18,491 --> 00:21:21,914
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

308
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:28,530
What do you think? This is so cool, isn't it?

309
00:21:28,530 --> 00:21:30,632
If you want to look cool, let me know.

310
00:21:30,632 --> 00:21:31,984
I'll let you borrow it.

311
00:21:31,984 --> 00:21:33,694
Do you even know how to ride it?

312
00:21:33,694 --> 00:21:34,938
Yes.

313
00:21:36,603 --> 00:21:39,164
- Can your feet touch the ground?
- Of course.

314
00:21:48,586 --> 00:21:51,270
I'm not going to fall off.

315
00:21:57,237 --> 00:22:00,112
Hey, hey, hey!

316
00:22:00,112 --> 00:22:03,871
Hey!

317
00:22:13,915 --> 00:22:15,915
- I'm sorry.
- I should be the one to say sorry.

318
00:22:15,915 --> 00:22:17,732
Why would you say sorry? It was an accident.

319
00:22:17,732 --> 00:22:20,107
- But you apologized to me first.
- That's true.

320
00:22:20,825 --> 00:22:23,335
I was a bit too careless. I'm not used to this.

321
00:22:23,335 --> 00:22:24,729
Off you go.

322
00:22:24,729 --> 00:22:27,001
I can't go. You're holding my hands.

323
00:22:29,552 --> 00:22:31,268
I have to go take care of something.

324
00:22:31,268 --> 00:22:32,967
Do you remember the way back?

325
00:22:32,967 --> 00:22:34,967
Yes, I'll be totally fine.

326
00:22:34,967 --> 00:22:38,720
Be careful though. My bike is powerful.
You might not be able to keep up.

327
00:22:48,785 --> 00:22:53,521
It was an accident. It was an accident.
It was an accident.

328
00:22:53,521 --> 00:22:54,712
Let's go.

329
00:23:02,469 --> 00:23:04,469
Hey, what are you doing?

330
00:23:04,469 --> 00:23:06,362
Shrimp paste fried rice?

331
00:23:06,362 --> 00:23:07,593
Cute.

332
00:23:08,728 --> 00:23:10,614
Me?

333
00:23:10,614 --> 00:23:12,362
I meant the picture.

334
00:23:14,116 --> 00:23:17,764
If only you'd started school this year,
you'd do well.

335
00:23:17,764 --> 00:23:19,528
Stop talking about this.

336
00:23:19,528 --> 00:23:21,383
I made my decision a long time ago.

337
00:23:22,880 --> 00:23:26,053
Kang, come help me carry...

338
00:23:26,053 --> 00:23:27,202
- Okay.
- Neth!

339
00:23:27,202 --> 00:23:28,138
Have you eaten?

340
00:23:28,138 --> 00:23:29,913
Not yet, Mom. I'm hungry.

341
00:23:29,913 --> 00:23:31,744
Let me fix you up.

342
00:23:31,744 --> 00:23:34,840
Don't cook for her, Mom,
or she'll eat up all the rice in the cooker.

343
00:23:34,840 --> 00:23:36,026
This one is a greedy eater.

344
00:23:36,026 --> 00:23:37,825
You're so mean to your friend.

345
00:23:37,825 --> 00:23:39,174
Can I have two fried eggs?

346
00:23:39,174 --> 00:23:40,694
You got it.

347
00:23:44,871 --> 00:23:48,032
By the way, where did you go?

348
00:23:48,032 --> 00:23:50,385
I dropped someone off at the bicycle shop.

349
00:23:52,365 --> 00:23:53,592
Who?

350
00:23:53,592 --> 00:23:55,158
I don't know.

351
00:23:55,158 --> 00:24:00,432
He randomly walked in here and
asked if I had a toothbrush for sale.

352
00:24:00,432 --> 00:24:03,675
Then he also asked me
if there's a bicycle shop nearby.

353
00:24:07,440 --> 00:24:10,026
Oh, that boy in a green shirt, right?

354
00:24:10,026 --> 00:24:10,934
Yes.

355
00:24:10,934 --> 00:24:12,392
He's my new tenant.

356
00:24:12,392 --> 00:24:15,432
He's from Bangkok.
His mom just dropped him off this morning.

357
00:24:15,432 --> 00:24:18,598
But it seems to me his mom sent him here
to discipline him.

358
00:24:18,598 --> 00:24:20,432
He looks like a troublemaker.

359
00:24:20,432 --> 00:24:22,183
Discipline?

360
00:24:22,183 --> 00:24:25,432
When I met him, he didn't seem like a bad person.

361
00:24:25,432 --> 00:24:29,005
Oh, you innocent guy.

362
00:24:29,005 --> 00:24:32,793
Even you, who seem like a good guy,
have a bad mouth.

363
00:24:32,793 --> 00:24:34,793
You're no different.

364
00:24:34,793 --> 00:24:35,893
Neth.

365
00:24:35,893 --> 00:24:37,000
- Neth, dear.
- Yes?

366
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:40,273
- Your rice is ready. It's warm and nice.
- Thank you, Mom.

367
00:24:40,273 --> 00:24:42,232
See, Mom? She's going to suck us dry.

368
00:24:42,232 --> 00:24:44,915
Two fried eggs, right? Here you go.
Can you really finish it?

369
00:24:44,915 --> 00:24:47,742
- Yes, I can. Thank you.
- Your body is still in great shape.

370
00:24:54,792 --> 00:24:56,713
[Mommy Kai's Rice and Curry]

371
00:25:00,073 --> 00:25:01,395
Thank you.

372
00:25:15,552 --> 00:25:16,953
Why is he not back yet?

373
00:25:21,643 --> 00:25:24,552
Hey. What happened?

374
00:25:24,552 --> 00:25:28,431
A frog ran in front of me.
I veered off and the chain came off.

375
00:25:30,432 --> 00:25:32,449
I also got this wound.

376
00:25:32,449 --> 00:25:34,127
You have to live with it.

377
00:25:34,127 --> 00:25:38,590
The young frogs are impatient around here.
They always run in front of people's vehicles.

378
00:25:43,435 --> 00:25:46,646
Thank you. If it weren't for you,
I'd be in a tough situation.

379
00:25:46,646 --> 00:25:48,647
Don't thank me. I'm charging you for everything.

380
00:25:48,647 --> 00:25:50,661
I'll put it on your tab later.

381
00:25:52,426 --> 00:25:54,880
Hey. Where are you taking my bike?

382
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:58,225
You think you can ride in that state?
You won't even be able to walk back.

383
00:26:03,025 --> 00:26:06,899
Why are you still sitting there? Get on.

384
00:26:06,899 --> 00:26:08,358
Do you want to go back to your dorm or not?

385
00:26:08,358 --> 00:26:09,414
Yes.

386
00:26:25,897 --> 00:26:27,924
- We've arrived.
- Yeah.

387
00:26:36,219 --> 00:26:37,969
How do I get this off?

388
00:26:42,608 --> 00:26:44,375
Come on. Let me help.

389
00:26:56,204 --> 00:27:00,477
Thank you for helping me and
dropping me off all the way here.

390
00:27:03,434 --> 00:27:05,634
Do you have something in your room
to clean your wound?

391
00:27:07,672 --> 00:27:09,000
See you later then.

392
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:12,789
Go put your bike away. I'll wait at my restaurant.

393
00:27:12,789 --> 00:27:13,980
Okay.

394
00:27:21,061 --> 00:27:24,040
You're overreacting. I'll put it away myself.

395
00:27:30,407 --> 00:27:32,031
He's quite kind.

396
00:27:48,434 --> 00:27:50,934
Ouch. That stings.

397
00:27:56,107 --> 00:27:57,394
It will sting a bit.

398
00:28:02,356 --> 00:28:03,984
It hurts.

399
00:28:03,984 --> 00:28:05,954
Don't move.

400
00:28:39,100 --> 00:28:40,315
Done.

401
00:28:41,035 --> 00:28:43,872
Thank you. If it weren't for you,
I'd be in a bad condition.

402
00:28:43,872 --> 00:28:48,178
I was just worried your wound would rot
and you'd have to cut off your arm.

403
00:28:48,178 --> 00:28:50,527
The doctors are busy around here.

404
00:28:50,527 --> 00:28:52,363
I don't want to give them more work.

405
00:28:58,293 --> 00:29:00,314
- Hey.
- Hmm?

406
00:29:00,314 --> 00:29:02,301
Your restaurant is still open, right?

407
00:29:02,301 --> 00:29:04,704
Of course. Are you hungry?

408
00:29:04,704 --> 00:29:05,791
Yeah.

409
00:29:09,523 --> 00:29:11,591
Wow.

410
00:29:12,407 --> 00:29:13,632
This is my dream fried egg.

411
00:29:13,632 --> 00:29:15,270
Why are you so skilled?

412
00:29:15,270 --> 00:29:17,070
Calm down. It's just a fried egg.

413
00:29:18,013 --> 00:29:19,373
I'm serious.

414
00:29:19,373 --> 00:29:22,393
Just by looking at it,
I can tell it's a crispy fried egg.

415
00:29:22,393 --> 00:29:23,664
Look at this.

416
00:29:24,975 --> 00:29:26,480
The egg yolk is undercooked.

417
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:28,978
This is the correct fried egg
by international standards.

418
00:29:28,978 --> 00:29:30,898
This is not a waste of being a fried egg.

419
00:29:38,129 --> 00:29:39,869
It's so yummy.

420
00:29:39,869 --> 00:29:42,348
Did your mom leave you with a phone
when you were a kid?

421
00:29:42,348 --> 00:29:44,391
Your reaction is so over the top.

422
00:29:44,391 --> 00:29:46,713
It's just a fried egg,
but you rave so much about it.

423
00:29:46,713 --> 00:29:49,274
You're not originally from Nakhon Pathom, right?

424
00:29:49,274 --> 00:29:50,368
No.

425
00:29:51,144 --> 00:29:53,166
I just moved here from Bangkok.

426
00:29:53,166 --> 00:29:54,953
I transferred here for 12th grade.

427
00:29:54,953 --> 00:29:56,640
So you're sent here to correct your behavior.

428
00:29:56,640 --> 00:29:59,400
You talk like you knew.

429
00:30:00,660 --> 00:30:02,908
This is literally so delicious.

430
00:30:02,908 --> 00:30:04,435
I'm not kidding.

431
00:30:19,762 --> 00:30:20,913
How much is the food?

432
00:30:20,913 --> 00:30:23,563
I'd usually charge 1,000 baht
but you said it's delicious,

433
00:30:23,563 --> 00:30:25,335
so I'm only charging you 45 baht.

434
00:30:25,335 --> 00:30:26,513
Alright.

435
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:32,835
- Do you accept a bank transfer?
- Sure.

436
00:30:34,061 --> 00:30:37,467
But I don't know if the internet signal is good.

437
00:30:38,583 --> 00:30:40,583
The signal at your restaurant
is better than in my room.

438
00:30:40,583 --> 00:30:43,634
I don't want to complain,
but there's only one bar upstairs.

439
00:30:43,634 --> 00:30:46,237
I'll find an excuse to come
and use the internet here again.

440
00:30:49,696 --> 00:30:51,938
Just a moment.
[Available Balance: 30.50]

441
00:30:59,016 --> 00:31:01,016
What's up, Moo?

442
00:31:01,016 --> 00:31:03,348
The day is not over yet
and you're missing me already?

443
00:31:03,348 --> 00:31:04,937
I miss you.

444
00:31:04,937 --> 00:31:10,081
Mom, can you transfer money to me?
I spent all the money to buy a new bike.

445
00:31:10,081 --> 00:31:11,759
How is that possible?

446
00:31:11,759 --> 00:31:13,388
Your account has like 10,000,

447
00:31:13,388 --> 00:31:16,404
and I already transferred
an additional 5,000 for this month.

448
00:31:16,404 --> 00:31:18,979
My bike cost almost 20,000.

449
00:31:18,979 --> 00:31:21,028
What kind of crazy bike cost 20,000?

450
00:31:21,028 --> 00:31:25,372
I didn't send you there
to live comfortably day by day.

451
00:31:25,372 --> 00:31:27,919
You have to be frugal. Do you understand?

452
00:31:27,919 --> 00:31:29,683
You're not supposed to spend your time going out.

453
00:31:29,683 --> 00:31:31,657
Mom, I'm not going out.

454
00:31:31,657 --> 00:31:33,693
The bicycle is an essential item.

455
00:31:33,693 --> 00:31:36,787
Without it, I'd have to walk until my legs hurt.

456
00:31:36,787 --> 00:31:39,210
I don't know and I won't give you any more money.

457
00:31:39,210 --> 00:31:42,070
I already transferred you this month's allowance.

458
00:31:42,070 --> 00:31:44,366
I'll transfer again next month.

459
00:31:44,366 --> 00:31:47,199
You must survive. This is your test.

460
00:31:47,199 --> 00:31:49,528
Mom, I really don't have money.

461
00:31:49,528 --> 00:31:52,514
Mom! Are you really not going to give me money?

462
00:31:52,514 --> 00:31:53,944
Mom!

463
00:31:53,944 --> 00:31:55,760
Please, Mom!

464
00:31:55,760 --> 00:31:57,357
Mom!

465
00:31:57,357 --> 00:32:00,120
Mew, my best friend, do you have
one or two thousand baht I could borrow?

466
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:01,442
I'm really broke now.

467
00:32:01,442 --> 00:32:03,165
Hello, Pike. Can I borrow 1,000 baht?

468
00:32:03,165 --> 00:32:05,100
Hello, Wit. Damn it!

469
00:32:14,752 --> 00:32:17,309
If you're going to pay me with this many coins,
I don't want it.

470
00:32:17,309 --> 00:32:19,853
No one is having an ordination ceremony.
Keep them for the water vendor machine.

471
00:32:19,853 --> 00:32:23,069
I only have coins and these are all I have.

472
00:32:23,069 --> 00:32:25,360
You can pay me later.

473
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:28,621
Really? Will you really let me pay later?

474
00:32:34,210 --> 00:32:35,909
I promise I won't run from my debt.

475
00:32:35,909 --> 00:32:37,997
I'll definitely pay you back one day.

476
00:32:39,988 --> 00:32:42,505
Are you sure? You owe me 10 million already...

477
00:32:42,505 --> 00:32:45,993
for the toothbrush, the ride, fixing your bike,
dressing your wound, and the food.

478
00:32:45,993 --> 00:32:48,629
Are you serious? I thought you were joking.

479
00:32:49,448 --> 00:32:52,937
I'll put it on your tab.

480
00:32:52,937 --> 00:32:54,545
What's your name?

481
00:32:54,545 --> 00:32:56,474
Are you tricking me into telling you my name?

482
00:32:56,474 --> 00:32:57,603
Your name is Little Brat.

483
00:32:57,603 --> 00:32:59,989
My name is Moo.

484
00:32:59,989 --> 00:33:01,272
What's your name?

485
00:33:03,942 --> 00:33:07,197
You have no right to ask.
Why do you want to know?

486
00:33:07,973 --> 00:33:12,152
So I can make a note on my phone
of who I owe money to,

487
00:33:12,152 --> 00:33:14,015
but if you don't tell me your name,

488
00:33:14,015 --> 00:33:18,273
I'll write that I owe money
to Bad-Mouth-Kind-Heart Bro.

489
00:33:18,273 --> 00:33:20,527
I'm not kind.

490
00:33:20,527 --> 00:33:22,927
You gave me the toothbrush,

491
00:33:22,927 --> 00:33:24,673
took me to the bicycle shop,

492
00:33:24,673 --> 00:33:26,873
fixed my bike, dressed my wound,

493
00:33:26,873 --> 00:33:28,513
and gave me food.

494
00:33:28,513 --> 00:33:33,891
If that's not kind,
should I call you Cute Bro instead?

495
00:33:33,891 --> 00:33:36,233
You're not Little Brat, but Pain in the Neck.

496
00:33:36,233 --> 00:33:38,193
- I call it quick-witted.
- Argumentative.

497
00:33:38,193 --> 00:33:39,421
Please stop.

498
00:33:47,042 --> 00:33:50,525
Even though I owe you money
and can't pay you back,

499
00:33:50,525 --> 00:33:54,878
let me repay you by doing what I do best.

500
00:34:04,086 --> 00:34:08,742
♫ My heart sparks when you turn around ♫

501
00:34:08,742 --> 00:34:13,974
♫ Once our eyes meet, I'm so down ♫

502
00:34:13,974 --> 00:34:16,912
♫ I'm not one to fall easily ♫

503
00:34:16,912 --> 00:34:21,774
♫ But my heart's in trouble now, you see ♫

504
00:34:21,774 --> 00:34:25,968
♫ I'm all yours only ♫

505
00:34:27,652 --> 00:34:30,152
♫ Yours only ♫

506
00:34:36,779 --> 00:34:39,608
Ouch! It hurts.

507
00:34:53,374 --> 00:34:54,819
Thank you.

508
00:35:09,334 --> 00:35:12,827
Mosquito. Of all the places to bite,
you're biting my face?

509
00:35:12,827 --> 00:35:14,776
You're going to get it.

510
00:35:14,776 --> 00:35:15,905
Stop!

511
00:35:15,905 --> 00:35:19,262
Why would you slap it? You can just shoo it away.

512
00:35:19,262 --> 00:35:22,611
You're lucky the cute guy's words
saved your life, little mosquito.

513
00:35:22,611 --> 00:35:23,813
Go away.

514
00:35:31,753 --> 00:35:34,886
[Little Brat Pain in the Neck, Argumentative]

515
00:35:36,856 --> 00:35:39,029
My name is Moo.

516
00:35:39,029 --> 00:35:40,601
What's your name?

517
00:35:40,601 --> 00:35:42,308
Why do you want to know?

518
00:35:42,308 --> 00:35:46,663
So I can make a note on my phone
who I owe money to,

519
00:35:46,663 --> 00:35:48,320
but if you don't tell me your name,

520
00:35:48,320 --> 00:35:52,553
I'll write that I owe money
to Bad-Mouth-Kind-Heart Bro.

521
00:35:52,553 --> 00:35:54,746
I'm not kind.

522
00:35:54,746 --> 00:35:57,230
You gave me the toothbrush,

523
00:35:57,230 --> 00:35:58,845
took me to the bicycle shop,

524
00:35:58,845 --> 00:36:01,277
fixed my bike, dressed my wound,

525
00:36:01,277 --> 00:36:02,793
and gave me food.

526
00:36:02,793 --> 00:36:07,633
If that's not kind,
should I call you Cute Bro instead?

527
00:36:40,381 --> 00:36:42,519
[Mommy Kai's Rice And Curry]

528
00:37:20,897 --> 00:37:22,362
What are you drawing, son?

529
00:37:23,035 --> 00:37:24,152
Oh.

530
00:37:25,828 --> 00:37:27,311
You're drawing our restaurant?

531
00:37:28,623 --> 00:37:30,944
I'm practicing coloring.

532
00:37:30,944 --> 00:37:32,668
It's quite hard.

533
00:37:32,668 --> 00:37:35,721
If you mess up on coloring on
this kind of paper, you can't fix it.

534
00:37:35,721 --> 00:37:37,772
You're right.

535
00:37:39,764 --> 00:37:41,454
- Dad.
- Hmm?

536
00:37:41,454 --> 00:37:43,888
- I want a tablet.
- A tablet?

537
00:37:43,888 --> 00:37:48,279
What would you use a tablet for?
You just draw casually.

538
00:37:51,525 --> 00:37:55,739
Mom, how many times have I told you
I don't draw casually?

539
00:37:56,959 --> 00:38:01,782
Are you serious about getting into art school?

540
00:38:01,782 --> 00:38:03,976
You might want to think it over.

541
00:38:03,976 --> 00:38:09,178
What's wrong with me wanting
to study art and become an artist?

542
00:38:09,178 --> 00:38:10,368
Kang.

543
00:38:11,587 --> 00:38:13,329
Take it easy.

544
00:38:13,329 --> 00:38:16,752
Your mom just wants you to take time
to think about this.

545
00:38:16,752 --> 00:38:18,179
You still have time.

546
00:38:18,179 --> 00:38:19,397
Yes.

547
00:38:27,521 --> 00:38:28,869
Kind?

548
00:38:30,750 --> 00:38:32,052
I don't think so.

549
00:38:42,560 --> 00:38:46,497
♫ You tell me not to take it seriously,
but you secretly do ♫

550
00:38:46,497 --> 00:38:51,434
♫ A bit cuter than this
and I'll become your slave ♫

551
00:38:51,434 --> 00:38:52,466
Hey.

552
00:38:53,092 --> 00:38:57,125
Why is he wearing a jacket?
Won't he die from the heat?

553
00:38:57,125 --> 00:38:58,628
What a poser.

554
00:38:58,628 --> 00:39:01,337
Judging from his look,
he must have gotten expelled.

555
00:39:15,770 --> 00:39:16,985
Hey, kid.

556
00:39:17,861 --> 00:39:18,861
Yes?

557
00:39:19,528 --> 00:39:21,869
This is my usual parking spot. Move.

558
00:39:23,283 --> 00:39:24,629
I don't see any names here.

559
00:39:24,629 --> 00:39:25,993
First come, first served.

560
00:39:26,998 --> 00:39:28,573
Why are you talking like this?

561
00:39:30,085 --> 00:39:31,780
You must be new.

562
00:39:32,469 --> 00:39:34,478
That's why you don't know who we are.

563
00:39:34,478 --> 00:39:35,573
Who are you guys?

564
00:39:35,573 --> 00:39:39,053
We're the people you don't want to cross
because we can make your life here a living hell.

565
00:39:39,053 --> 00:39:40,459
You think you're so important?

566
00:39:42,338 --> 00:39:44,574
- What?
- What are you doing to my bike?

567
00:39:44,574 --> 00:39:45,574
Hey.

568
00:39:48,470 --> 00:39:49,948
Don't fight!

569
00:39:51,548 --> 00:39:53,757
Nothing is going on, Mr. Security Guard.

570
00:39:53,757 --> 00:39:55,500
Hello, Director.

571
00:39:57,399 --> 00:39:58,463
Hi.

572
00:40:00,648 --> 00:40:02,120
Do I look like a security guard?

573
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:06,722
[Pathom Pittaya School]

574
00:40:16,198 --> 00:40:17,977
Oh. Okay.

575
00:40:17,977 --> 00:40:19,015
Remove it.

576
00:40:19,967 --> 00:40:22,716
You're here to study, not to look handsome, okay?

577
00:40:22,716 --> 00:40:25,477
If you want to look handsome,
do that outside the school.

578
00:40:27,455 --> 00:40:31,595
Your last semester grades from
your previous school weren't very good.

579
00:40:31,595 --> 00:40:34,499
But I think I did much better
than when I was in grade 11.

580
00:40:34,499 --> 00:40:37,244
2.0 is not good.

581
00:40:37,244 --> 00:40:39,583
It's called a borderline pass. Got it?

582
00:40:39,583 --> 00:40:41,180
Yeah.

583
00:40:41,180 --> 00:40:42,622
But it's okay.

584
00:40:42,622 --> 00:40:45,339
Your mom has asked me to help you with this.

585
00:40:45,339 --> 00:40:48,314
Even though you're only going
to be here for one semester,

586
00:40:48,314 --> 00:40:51,083
I want you to adjust.

587
00:40:51,083 --> 00:40:56,848
I understand that a sudden change
can make you feel uncomfortable,

588
00:40:56,848 --> 00:40:59,554
but that's how life is.

589
00:40:59,554 --> 00:41:02,815
Unexpected changes can happen all the time.

590
00:41:02,815 --> 00:41:05,950
This might be your first time,
so it'll be a bit difficult.

591
00:41:05,950 --> 00:41:10,558
When I had to move back from New York
to teach in Thailand,

592
00:41:10,558 --> 00:41:13,774
I had to adjust myself a lot too because
I was only familiar with the English language.

593
00:41:13,774 --> 00:41:15,222
- What's "see luang" in English?
- Yellow.

594
00:41:15,222 --> 00:41:16,193
Chopping knife in Thai? Ito.

595
00:41:16,193 --> 00:41:18,279
Earthen stove in Thai? Anglo.

596
00:41:18,279 --> 00:41:20,680
- This is not the time to make jokes.
- I'm sorry.

597
00:41:20,680 --> 00:41:28,209
Let me tell you that all changes
come with discomfort,

598
00:41:28,209 --> 00:41:31,702
but do you know how I got through those times?

599
00:41:33,380 --> 00:41:34,556
I have no idea.

600
00:41:35,939 --> 00:41:39,449
You have to find happiness in change.

601
00:41:40,482 --> 00:41:45,142
That happiness will help you
get through tough times.

602
00:41:46,025 --> 00:41:47,705
Remember my words.

603
00:41:50,479 --> 00:41:53,148
I will. Thank you.

604
00:41:53,148 --> 00:41:54,443
Anything else?

605
00:41:55,581 --> 00:41:56,842
- Director.
- Hmm?

606
00:41:56,842 --> 00:41:59,060
Can I borrow 200 baht?

607
00:41:59,060 --> 00:42:00,445
Oh my god.

608
00:42:24,926 --> 00:42:26,334
Hey.

609
00:42:26,334 --> 00:42:28,135
You sell rice and curry here too?

610
00:42:28,135 --> 00:42:29,206
Hey.

611
00:42:29,924 --> 00:42:31,071
You again?

612
00:42:31,071 --> 00:42:33,156
Hi, Bad-Mouth-Kind-Heart Bro.

613
00:42:33,156 --> 00:42:34,952
That's not my name.

614
00:42:34,952 --> 00:42:37,018
What's your name then? You haven't told me.

615
00:42:40,750 --> 00:42:42,247
Who's even called Stir-Fried Clams?

616
00:42:44,571 --> 00:42:45,801
Kang.

617
00:42:46,659 --> 00:42:48,138
My name is Kang.

618
00:42:48,882 --> 00:42:50,267
Kang.

619
00:42:51,626 --> 00:42:53,940
Let me officially introduce myself.

620
00:42:53,940 --> 00:42:56,568
My name is Mok. My nickname is Moo.

621
00:42:56,568 --> 00:42:59,156
Nice to meet you, bro.

622
00:43:00,416 --> 00:43:01,433
Mm.

623
00:43:03,284 --> 00:43:06,743
You have to find happiness in change.

624
00:43:06,743 --> 00:43:11,613
That happiness will help you
get through tough times.

625
00:43:11,613 --> 00:43:14,113
I found my happiness.

626
00:43:34,657 --> 00:43:37,805
Actually, being punished to live alone
is not as hard as I thought.

627
00:43:37,805 --> 00:43:39,647
Wait. Do you know how to wash the dishes?

628
00:43:39,647 --> 00:43:42,636
You live alone now.
You must learn to rely on yourself, you know?

629
00:43:42,636 --> 00:43:43,962
I have you, Kang.

630
00:43:43,962 --> 00:43:46,097
Let's call it a day. I'm tired.

631
00:43:46,097 --> 00:43:47,236
Not yet.

632
00:43:47,236 --> 00:43:48,398
My moves are still awkward.

633
00:43:48,398 --> 00:43:51,588
My mom gave me an ultimatum
to study hard and not get distracted.

634
00:43:51,588 --> 00:43:53,295
I don't want to hurt her feelings.

635
00:43:53,295 --> 00:43:57,713
But we can work towards dreams
and reality at the same time, right?

636
00:43:57,713 --> 00:44:00,960
No one can stop your dream, except yourself.

637
00:44:00,960 --> 00:44:04,898
Things are not difficult
because you're there for me.
